I can rant about this topic for pages. I will however just offer my short version.<P>I am tired of parents who are willing to blame everyone but themselves. If parents took some responsibility in regards to parenting, I think we'd have less school violence. I don't know what happened to people taking some active participation in their childrens' lives, but that's obviously a thing of the past.<P>Also, here's my 2 cents on bullies and such. There have always been bullies, and there will probably always be bullies. I was tortured as a child, but at least, at the end of the day, I could go home to my family, and they made me feel special and wonderful and loved. I think these days, kids go to school, they get picked on, then they come home and they don't have that same kind of support. It's just sad.<P>Video games don't make kids kill, poor parenting makes kids kill.<P>--------------------<P>Esseilte Blacstaff<BR>Head Recruiting Officer, Guardians of Magic<BR>Druidess of Tunare and Happiest Woman in all of Norrath!
