I'd have to agree with the lawsuit-crazed society we have now, in general.  Idiots like the woman that sued Jack Daniels for her babies birth defects, because she didn't know drinking a 5th a day while pregnant would be harmful, make the whole process seem like a sham.  <P>Concerning the link posted originally, did they fail to mention that "Doom" is based on killing <I>aliens</I> - and that's not "illegal" aliens, either.  How does shooting demon-looking beings hurling balls of energy at your character supposed to translate into taking a shotgun to school?  The kids would have to be on mushrooms or LSD to tie the two together.  The movie "(The?)Basketball Diaries", with Leonardo Di Caprio, has more likeness to the Columbine incident than a video game does.  In one scene he explicity pulls out a shotgun and starts unloading on his teacher and classmates.  Guess I missed that level in Doom.   <IMG SRC="rolleyes.gif" border="0"><P>Another interesting thing to think about concerning parentage...  It takes more credentials to get a driver's license or even set up an EQ account (CC or bank account) than it does to have a child - or be a parent.  What if the parents themselves had bad, absentee, or abusive parenting?  Can they sue their parents for the way their own kids turned out?  It makes wonder in amazement why people even have children if they basically abandon, abuse or hate the idea of having kids.  If they're going to rely on somebody else to raise them then why don't they make arrangements from the beginning with adoptive services??  Ridiculous.    <IMG SRC="mad.gif" border="0"><P>Gravelgut:  That's horrible what happened to your sister-in-law, and the M.D. should be reprimanded, even dis-barred (or whatever the medical term is called), because he would have to "sign off" on his recommendaton - or lack of it.  The only thing I do question is:  Did your sister-in-law or her husband (in her behalf) seek a second opinion?  On anything as important as that I'd <I>definitely</I> seek other counsel, <I>especially</I> if I felt the problem wasn't being dealt with correctly.<P>--------------------<P>"Time flies like an arrow; fruit flies like a banana."
